            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "Yes—annual maintenance prevents 80% of AC breakdowns and extends system life 30-50%. Most AC failures develop gradually over months or years through refrigerant leaks, electrical connection deterioration, capacitor weakening, coil fouling, and lubrication breakdown. Professional maintenance catches these developing issues when they're inexpensive to address rather than waiting for system failure during peak summer heat when repairs cost more and leave you uncomfortable for days. Maintenance also maintains efficiency—dirty coils, low refrigerant, and poor airflow increase operating costs 15-30% even when system appears to work fine. Maintenance typically costs $119-189 annually but saves $200-400 yearly through improved efficiency, prevents $800-2,500 emergency repairs, and extends system life 3-7 years saving $5,000-12,000 in premature replacement. Skipping maintenance voids most manufacturer warranties, risks summertime system failure when contractors are busiest, and turns minor $150 repairs into major $1,500+ failures. Maintenance is the single best investment in HVAC reliability and efficiency."
